network_overview: The capture contains only SIP signaling for two parallel VoLTE call attempts that both fail: the first pair is cancelled after ~26 s, the second pair times out after <1 s. All four calls stop at 180 Ringing; no RTP bearer is established, so no voice path ever exists.

observations.finding: 100 % of INVITE transactions end in failure; 4×407 Proxy Authentication Required followed by 2×487 Request Terminated and 2× invite-timeout.
No RTP flows detected; media bearer never set up, hence zero voice minutes delivered.
Every first INVITE is challenged with 407, but second INVITE carries no visible Proxy-Authorization header in the decoded trace, suggesting UE or P-CSCF does not retry with credentials.
Post-180 Ringing, neither call receives 200 OK within ~25 s, causing user-initiated CANCEL or client timeout; indicates downstream S-CSCF/TAS or called-party alerting problem.

root_causes.description: P-CSCF challenges each initial INVITE with SIP 407, but the re-INVITE either omits credentials or the S-CSCF rejects them, so the call cannot proceed to 200 OK.
root_causes.impact: All VoLTE calls fail at setup phase; subscribers cannot originate voice.

root_causes.description: After 180 Ringing is sent, no 200 OK arrives within 25 s, forcing the originating UE to CANCEL or timeout.
root_causes.impact: Even if authentication were fixed, calls would still fail to connect; affects answer-seizure ratio.

recommendations.action: Check P-CSCF/UE logs to verify that the second INVITE carries a valid Proxy-Authorization header; if missing, update UE IMS configuration or ISIM credentials.
recommendations.rationale: Eliminates the 407 loop and allows INVITE to reach S-CSCF.

recommendations.action: Trace the downstream leg (Mw/Mg) from S-CSCF toward called-party IMS/TAS to discover why 200 OK is never returned after 180 Ringing.
recommendations.rationale: Fixes the second failure point once authentication succeeds.

recommendations.action: Validate that the Rx interface between P-CSCF and PCRF creates the dedicated bearer (QCI=1) so RTP resources are reserved even before 200 OK.
recommendations.rationale: Ensures media path is ready and reduces post-answer delay.

session_analysis.signaling_health: Control-plane SIP messages flow correctly up to 180 Ringing, but every transaction is terminated prematurely (487 or timeout).
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP-U tunnels, no RTP streams; data plane is idle.
session_analysis.voice_quality: No bearer established → no MOS, packet-loss, or jitter metrics; service is unusable.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling failure prevents bearer creation; therefore user-plane remains silent.
